Rating: 3
We enjoyed this dish, though I tweaked it - I think the basic recipe could be taken in a bunch of different directions. I didn't have fresh basil or thyme, so I substituted cilantro. I also added garlic, red pepper flakes, and cumin to the green onion. Like the cook from Arlington, I marinated the shrimp (but in olive oil, lemon juice, s/p), seared them, and then added them to the rice. I think I'll use this recipe for its basic idea and play with it some more!

