Rating: 3
This is REALLY good, and easy! I love corn and shrimp, but was surprised by how much depth of flavor this dish has. I've made some substitutions with great success: I substituted a small shallot for the white part of the green onions, and chopped chives for the green part; I marinated the shrimp briefly in white wine and a tiny bit of olive oil, then seared them and added to the rice at the last minute; I added some peeled diced tomato with the shrimp; and finally, added a little cayenne for kick. Yummy!

